🎈Balloon garland tips:
Tie together clusters of 2 and 3 balloons. Next, wrap them around each other to make clusters of 4 and 5. Then, tie your balloon clusters together using fishing line by wrapping it around the balloons in a figure 8 motion. To easily hang your balloon clusters on the wall, use command hooks with fishing line. For this garland, I used 2 command hooks and tied a piece of fishing line from one to the next. Then I tied the balloon clusters to it. You can also build the entire garland before you hang it, but since I built this design as I went, this method worked great!
.

🍫Chocolate Potted Flowers🌷
.
These make the cutest spring desserts and are a great way to elevate your table setting!
.
You’ll need:
A silicone lollipop mold
Lollipop sticks
Chocolate and/or Candy Melts
Mini flower pots (add ribbon if you like)
Egg carton cutouts or floral foam for the base
Easter grass
.
Pour your center color in first. I put the melted chocolate in a ziplock bag, then cut the tip off and used that to squeeze it in. Freeze or refrigerate the mold until the center hardens (keep it flat). Then add your second layer of melted chocolate to complete your flowers & add in lollipop sticks. Tap your flower molds on the counter to get out the air bubbles. Freeze or refrigerate until they harden. Insert chocolate flowers into the pots by placing the sticks into upside down egg carton cutouts topped with Easter grass. Then you’ll have these cute potted chocolate flowers!

🔨When you learn to DIY baseboards for a room makeover. Before and after process…🪚
.
What do you think of the final result? I turned Adra’s old room into Ava’s new room! This was the only space in our house with these baseboards and I couldn’t stand them, so I bought a miter saw and figured out how to install new ones. I love how they turned out and they make such a huge difference to this space!!🙌
.
📌Steps I did for installing new baseboards:
.
▪️Sand, prime + paint boards before installing 
▪️Cut your exact measurements
▪️Miter joints for a seamless look
▪️Install with a nail gun or the old fashioned way like I did: hammer finishing nails, then use a nail set to drive the nail below the surface.
▪️Fill holes with wood filler, then sand flush.
▪️Caulk along the board tops and in each joint
▪️Touch up paint on holes
.
Ava picked the color scheme and had the final say in everything we chose for her room. It was so much fun to do together! The detailed videos of the whole process are in my story highlights “Ava’s Room Makeover”. Now I want to do more DIY house projects!😍

🍁DIY Dollar Tree Fall Candle🕯️
.
Make this cozy fall candle by grabbing a glass candle holder, some faux fall leaves, and an LED tea light candle. You’ll also need some Mod Podge and a foam brush.
.
Clean the glass with dish soap, then wipe down the outside of the glass with rubbing alcohol to remove any surface dirt or grease. Avoid touching the sides of the glass where the leaves are going to go so that they will stick. Iron your leaves flat, then brush a layer of Mod Podge on the outside of the glass. Let it sit for a few minutes until the glue gets sticky, then press on your leaves. After you have your leaves on, coat with another layer of Mod Podge. Once it dries, add your LED tea light and enjoy your new cozy fall candle!🍂
The last one also doubles as an easy costume idea!🧙‍♀️ These cute Amazon fall pieces are perfect for the season and can be styled various ways! Linked in my bio.

2 Simple & Spooky Hairstyles!
.
👁️Eyeball Bubble Braids👁️:
All you need is hair ties & eyeballs. Start with hair in pigtails, then stick an eyeball inside of each bubble braid, securing each one with a hair tie.
.
🕷️Spider Buns🕷️:
You’ll need: black hair ties, 8 pipe cleaners, 2 small pieces of black fabric & 2 sets of eyes to glue on. Start with pigtail braids, then wrap each one into a bun. Cover buns with a piece of fabric & secure it with a hair tie. Wrap 4 pipe cleaners around each bun & bend them to create spider legs, then hot glue eyeballs to each spider.

🕷️DIY Spooky Punch Bowl🧟‍♀️
.
Do you need an easy, last minute hit for Halloween? Grab a spider web bowl, a clear bowl, eyeballs & spiders (all from Dollar Tree). This makes a perfect punch or candy bowl! If you use it as a punch bowl, you’ll also need a ladle.
.
Bowl Instructions: Hot glue the bottom of the spider web bowl to the bottom of a clear bowl. Then hot glue spiders to the outside of the clear bowl.

✨DIY Lit Holiday Arrangement✨
.
You’ll need: 2 glass vases (a smaller and larger one), faux floral stems/branches/holly leaves, LED string lights, Mod Podge, a foam brush, and epsom salt. I found my floral stems/branches and LED string lights from Dollar Tree, and vases at goodwill. I used 3 sets of 10 light string lights (2 in vase and 1 in the floral branches). You may not need this many if you have a longer strand or if you don’t want it as lit up.
.
Instructions: Clean vases with dish soap, then wipe down the outside of the glass with rubbing alcohol to remove any surface dirt or grease. Avoid touching the sides of the glass where the leaves are going to go so that they’ll stick. Iron your holly leaves flat, then brush a layer of Mod Podge on the outside of the glass. Let it sit for a few minutes until the glue gets sticky, then press on your leaves. After your leaves are on, coat with another layer of Mod Podge. 
.
Fill the smaller vase with epsom salt (to hide the stems) and add your floral branches. Once the larger vase dries, set the smaller vase inside and add your LED string lights in between the vases. Add another string of LED lights in the top of the arrangement, tucking the battery pack into the arrangement.
